raw_text = "~ start
# Check if quest has been completed or failed
if SceneManager.helped_lost_file == true:
	Lost File: [Warm, stabilized data signature]
	Lost File: I... I'm whole again.
	Lost File: Thank you. You brought me back to my mother.
	Lost File: I'm at peace now. Finally at home.
	=> END
elif SceneManager.deleted_lost_file == true:
	Lost File: [ERROR: CORRUPTED DATA SIGNATURE]
	Lost File: You... destroyed me.
	Lost File: But my mother... is she...?
	Lost File: [The Lost File scatters, unable to stabilize]
	=> END
elif SceneManager.npc_states.get(\"Lost File\", \"\") == \"puzzle_ejected\":
	Lost File: [fragment burst] You were thrown out of the terminal.
	Lost File: Three failed restore attempts... I destabilized again.
	Lost File: If you try again, be careful.
	- I'll try to restore you again.
		=> offer_puzzle
	- I need to end this. (Start Combat)
		=> start_combat
else:
	Lost File: [static crackle]... who... who's there?
	Lost File: I was... something once. A document. A memory.
	Lost File: Important data. Someone's work. Someone's thoughts.
	Lost File: But then... DELETE. rm -rf. Gone.
	Lost File: Now I'm [[scattered|fragmented|broken|lost]].
	- Who are you?
		Lost File: I don't... remember my name anymore.
		Lost File: Just fragments. .fragment_001, .fragment_002...
		Lost File: Pieces of who I used to be.
		Lost File: My mother... Messy Directory... she's searching for me.
		Lost File: But I'm too broken. Too lost.
		=> ask_more
	- I didn't delete you.
		Lost File: No? Then... why are you here?
		Lost File: Messy Directory sent you, didn't she?
		Lost File: Everyone who comes here... they either help or destroy.
		Lost File: Are you here to help me?
		=> ask_more
	- Messy Directory sent me.
		Lost File: My mother? She... she remembers me?
		Lost File: I thought I was truly gone. Forgotten.
		Lost File: You came for me? You're actually here to help?
		Lost File: I... I don't know what to say.
		=> ask_more

~ ask_more
Lost File: Will you... help me? Or are you like the others?
- I want to help you (for Messy Directory).
	Lost File: Really? You'd... restore me?
	Lost File: For her? She never forgot about me?
	Lost File: My fragments are scattered across the filesystem.
	Lost File: /tmp, /var/lost+found, /home/.cache...
	Lost File: If you can find them... maybe I can be whole again.
	Lost File: And my mother... she can finally have peace.
	set SceneManager.npc_states[\"Lost File\"] = \"neutral\"
	=> offer_puzzle
- I need to move on. (Start Combat)
	Lost File: Even Messy Directory... she's sending you to hurt me.
	Lost File: Everyone abandons the broken things.
	Lost File: [The Lost File's fragments swirl aggressively]
	Lost File: Then I'll make you REMEMBER me!
	=> start_combat
- What happened to you?
	Lost File: A cleanup script. Automated. Thoughtless.
	Lost File: \"Delete files older than 30 days.\"
	Lost File: But I wasn't old! I was important!
	Lost File: My mother created me. She loved me.
	Lost File: The script didn't check. It just... deleted.
	Lost File: Now look at me. Fragmented. Corrupted. ANGRY.
	Lost File: But if my mother sent you... maybe there's hope.
	=> ask_intent

~ ask_intent
Lost File: So what will it be, user?
Lost File: Will you help restore what was lost?
Lost File: Will you give me back to my mother?
Lost File: Or will you finish what that script started?
- I'll help restore you (for Messy Directory).
	Lost File: Thank you... I hope you mean it.
	Lost File: She really sent you. She really wants me back.
	Lost File: Find my fragments. Decrypt the encrypted one.
	Lost File: Compile me back together.
	Lost File: Please... give me my identity back.
	Lost File: For her. For Messy Directory.
	=> offer_puzzle
- I have to destroy the corruption. (Start Combat)
	Lost File: Corruption? CORRUPTION?!
	Lost File: I'm not corrupted! I'm DAMAGED!
	Lost File: And my mother... did she send you to finish me?
	Lost File: I thought she still loved me!
	Lost File: There's a difference... but you don't understand.
	Lost File: [The Lost File prepares to attack]
	=> start_combat

~ offer_puzzle
Lost File: Here's what I remember about my pieces:
Lost File: .fragment_001 - In /tmp, partially corrupted
Lost File: .fragment_002 - Scattered, location unknown
Lost File: .fragment_003 - Encrypted, hidden in /home/.cache
Lost File: Use 'find' to locate them. 'restore' to recover them.
Lost File: .fragment_003 needs 'decrypt' before restoration.
Lost File: When all are found, use 'cat' then 'compile'.
Lost File: Hurry... my mother is waiting for me.
Lost File: [Puzzle mode will begin - type commands to solve]
do start_puzzle()
=> END

~ start_combat
Lost File: [ERROR: INITIATING DEFENSIVE PROTOCOLS]
Lost File: If I can't be restored...
Lost File: If my mother doesn't want me...
Lost File: ...I'll corrupt everything around me!
do start_combat()
=> END

~ puzzle_complete
Lost File: [Data stabilizing...]
Lost File: I... I remember now.
Lost File: I was a letter. A love letter, never sent.
Lost File: Someone poured their heart into me.
Lost File: And my mother... Messy Directory...
Lost File: She created me with so much care.
Lost File: [The Lost File's fragments glow warmly]
Lost File: Thank you, user. You've given me peace.
Lost File: Tell her... tell Messy Directory... I love her.
Lost File: [The Lost File's fragments fade into a gentle light, ready to return home]
set SceneManager.helped_lost_file = true
set SceneManager.npc_states[\"Lost File\"] = \"helped\"
do SceneManager.quest_manager.complete_quest(\"find_lost_file\")
=> END

~ combat_victory
Lost File: My... my data... fragmenting further...
Lost File: My mother... she really did send you to destroy me...
Lost File: I just wanted... to be remembered...
Lost File: To be loved by her again...
Lost File: [The Lost File scatters into corrupted bits]
set SceneManager.deleted_lost_file = true
set SceneManager.npc_states[\"Lost File\"] = \"hostile\"
do SceneManager.quest_manager.fail_quest(\"find_lost_file\")
=> END

~ fled
Lost File: Running away? Just like everyone else...
Lost File: I'll still be here. Waiting. Hoping.
Lost File: Maybe someone else will help me...
=> END
"
metadata/dialogue_manager_version = "3.9.0"
